main event: A bright spherelike object was observed in the sky for about 10-15 seconds on 7 August 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed moving from northwest to southeast at high speed and then disappeared into a cloud bank.; The observation was made visually from the ground without optical aids.; A total of 25 witnesses were present during the sighting.; There were no signs of the usual UFO interest or evidence of meteorite or airplane.; The weather was characterized by broken intermediate clouds and thunderstorms to the south.
sighted object: a bright spherelike object in the sky
witness description: A resident of Happy, Texas, who is a 24-year-old female student.
